"'''Gathering Shadows'''" is a short story by [[Kathy Burdette]] that details the experiences of a [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Rebel commando]] named [[Jai Raventhorn]] and a freelance [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary named]] [[Dirk Harkness]] sharing a [[Prison/Legends|cell]] together after an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] interrogation. The story takes place on [[Zelos II]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], two [[Standard month/Legends|months]] after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].

It was originally scheduled to be published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 16|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 16]], but the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal|''Adventure Journal'']] ceased publication before it could be featured, so it was later published in ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[December]] [[1999]].

==Plot summary==
[[Mercenary/Legends|Mercenary]] [[Dirk Harkness]] and [[New Republic Intelligence Service|New Republic Intelligence]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] [[Jai Raventhorn]] sit in a pitch-black [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Prison/Legends|prison cell]] recovering from interrogation. They are rescued by [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]] and [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance]] sympathizers [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] and [[Tru'eb Cholakk]], who braved the eerie landscape of [[Zelos II]] to find a secret Imperial [[Garrison/Legends|garrison]]. Jai, who is disillusioned by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], seriously considers Dirk's offer to become a mercenary and continue the fight against the Empire. 

==Continuity==
The quartet of protagonists featured in this story consisted of recurring characters from roleplaying game resource material published in the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' from [[West End Games]]. Their histories were previously detailed in a series of titled ''Star Wars'' stories ([[1994]]-[[1995|95]]) that appeared in the first six issues of that periodical.<ref name="TERC" />

